The paper discusses information-centric networking (ICN) and its potential benefits for improving the performance of IP-based services. This topic falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also touches on security (cs.CR) and architecture (cs.AR) considerations for implementing an IP-over-ICN proposition. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential impact on data centers (cs.DC) and information theory (cs.IT).
